articles.title: Macron, Biden Discuss Impact Of Wagner Rebellion On War: Elysee
articles.author: AFP
articles.excerpt: French President Emmanuel Macron discussed the Wagner rebellion's "possible impact" on the war in Ukraine with leaders including Joe Biden on Saturday, the Elysee said.
articles.summary:
By AFP - Agence France Presse
 
 
 June 24, 2023

 
 


 
 Order Reprints 
 
 Print Article 


 
 
 
 
 
French President Emmanuel Macron discussed the Wagner rebellion's "possible impact" on the war in Ukraine with leaders including Joe Biden on Saturday, the Elysee said.
 
Macron spoke with the US President as well as Polish President Andrzej Duda, German Chancellor Olaf Scholz and British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak.


 
"They also confirmed their commitment and determination to support Ukraine to allow it to recover its full sovereignty", the French Presidency said.

articles.title: US President Biden and European Leaders Discuss Crisis in Russia
articles.author: World
articles.excerpt: US President Joe Biden held a telephone conversation on Saturday with the leaders of France, Germany, and Britain to discuss the ongoing crisis in Russia. The crisis stems from the armed rebellion led by the Wagner Group, which began on Friday evening. In a statement, the White House announced that Biden and the European leaders […]
articles.summary:
US President Joe Biden held a telephone conversation on Saturday with the leaders of France, Germany, and Britain to discuss the ongoing crisis in Russia. The crisis stems from the armed rebellion led by the Wagner Group, which began on Friday evening.

In a statement, the White House announced that Biden and the European leaders discussed 'the situation in Russia ' and expressed their unwavering support for Ukraine. This comes as tensions continue to escalate in the region.

A spokesperson for the White House revealed that Biden, along with Vice President Kamala Harris and other senior US officials, received a briefing on the latest developments in Russia.
